 {"id":"wa-nu4.1.3","title":"[EPIC] Workflow: handle_usage_limits (Codex-first, safe pause + optional failover)","description":"# Workflow: handle_usage_limits (Codex-first)

## Goal
Respond to usage-limit reached events deterministically:
- ensure session is paused safely
- capture/resume metadata (session id, token usage)
- optionally perform credential/account failover and resume

## Why
Usage limits are the main operational friction when running agent fleets.

## Codex path (preferred when failover enabled)
Ctrl-C twice → parse token usage + resume id → select account via caut → device auth (Playwright) → resume session → send `proceed.`

## Safe fallback path
If failover is disabled or cannot complete (MFA):
- persist a structured "next steps" record
- mark pane/session state as UsageLimitReached with reset time
- optionally schedule a resume attempt at reset time

## Safety constraints
- all sends are PolicyEngine-gated
- workflow is step-logged so it can resume after restart



## Success Criteria
- Usage-limit events are detected and the workflow can safely pause/recover without spamming the terminal.
- Failover (when enabled) selects an account deterministically, completes device auth safely, and resumes the prior session.
- If interactive auth is required, the system fails safely with a clear next-step plan and artifacts.
- Tests include fixture-based parsers and a synthetic workflow run; E2E covers a dummy scenario with full logs.


## Testing
- Unit tests:
  - Parsers for usage-limit transcript variants (resume id, token usage, reset time) with a rich fixture set.
  - Decision logic: selecting next account deterministically (LRU + percent remaining tie-break).

- Synthetic workflow tests:
  - A fully synthetic run that exercises the full step plan without real auth:
    - validates guards (prompt active, not alt-screen, no gaps)
    - validates step logs are complete and redacted
    - validates safe fallback path produces a structured “next steps” record

- E2E:
  - Dummy/fixture-first E2E scenario with full artifacts via `wa-4vx.10.9`.
  - Separate “interactive auth required” negative E2E scenario should prove we fail safe and produce actionable artifacts.

## Acceptance Criteria
- All items in the following sections are satisfied: Success Criteria.
- All Testing requirements pass (unit/integration/E2E) with the logging/artifacts described above.
- Any explicit dependencies for this bead are implemented and validated via tests or E2E artifacts.

