-{"id":"wa-nu4.1.3.3","title":"Implement step: parse resume session id + token usage + reset time from pane tail","description":"# Task: Parse Codex session info (resume id + token usage + reset time)

## Goal
Extract structured session info needed to resume:
- `session_id` (UUID)
- token usage breakdown (prompt/completion/reasoning/cached when available)
- reset time (when printed)

## Inputs
- Current pane tail text.
  - Prefer stored segments + a small live `get-text` tail for freshness.

## Parser requirements
- Tolerate formatting drift:
  - numbers may contain commas
  - some token fields may be absent
  - cached tokens may be large and formatted as `(+ X cached)`
  - session id may appear in multiple forms (full UUID vs shortened)
- Never panic on unexpected formatting.
- Never log raw pane tail text (use hashes/redacted previews).

## Persistence
- Store parsed info in `agent_sessions` and/or workflow execution context:
  - enough to support `cod resume <session_id>`
  - enough to support account selection decisions and reporting

## Testing
- Unit tests:
  - a fixture corpus of real/expected Codex session summaries
  - fuzz-ish drift tests: missing fields, reordered lines, extra whitespace
- Integration tests:
  - “parse then persist”: upsert into `agent_sessions` and query back

## Acceptance Criteria
- Parser succeeds on known fixtures and produces stable structured output.
- Parser fails gracefully (structured error) when the required fields are absent, without leaking raw pane contents.
